==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|sg=[[point]] [[source]]}}

#{{science}} a source, especially of [[radiation]], [[wave]]s, fluid or other substance that has one specific location (and negligible physical extent, distinguishing a ''point source'' from other source geometries). In simulations they can often be approximated using mathematical point sources.
#(''pollution tracking'') a source of a pollutant, especially of [[radiation]], [[wave]]s, fluid or other substance that has one specific location (and negligible physical extent, distinguishing a ''point source'' from other pollution source geometries). In simulations they can often be approximated using mathematical point sources.
#{{mathematics}} a singularity emitting a flux or flow. A source with infinitesimal dimensions in space.

